jdrasil.workontd

Interface StateVectorFactory<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>


  • public interface StateVectorFactory<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    The \JClass{StateVectorFactory} is used to produce \JClass{StateVector} objects for \emph{leafs} of the tree decomposition. From there on, other \JClass{StateVector} objects are created directly by calling methods of the \JClass{StateVector} interface. Use an initialization of this interface to provide a dynamic program (i.\,e., a implementation of @see \JClass{StateVector}) to @see DynamicProgrammingOnTreeDecomposition.

      • createStateVectorForLeaf

        StateVector<T> createStateVectorForLeaf(int tw)
        Generate a \JClass{StateVector} object for a leaf of the tree-decomposition. These are usually empty, but may store the tree width of the graph or initialize some data structures.
        Parameters:
        tw - The tree width of the decomposition on which the dynamic program is executed.
        Returns:
        A \JClass{StateVector} object.
